The paper deals with learning visual feature representations for video analysis, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on automatic semantic description and captioning of video sequences, which is a task related to natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper introduces a novel multitask encoder-decoder framework, which involves training a visual encoder in a multitask fashion, and this is a task related to machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the Large Scale Movie Description Challenge (LSMDC) 2017, which is a task related to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper uses recurrent neural networks, which is a technique related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
